body.p: For assets and liabilities measured at fair value at the end of the reporting period, the IFRS requires quantitative disclosures about the fair value measurements for each class of assets and liabilities. An entity might disclose the following for assets to comply with paragraph 93(a) and (b) of the IFRS:

entry.none: Fair value measurements at the end of the reporting period using
Quoted prices in active markets for identical assets (Level 1)

entry.p: (Note: A similar table would be presented for liabilities unless another format is deemed more appropriate by the entity.)
